.TH "lpfc_setup_bg" 9 "lpfc_setup_bg" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
lpfc_setup_bg \- Setup Block guard structures and debug areas.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" lpfc_setup_bg
.BI "(struct lpfc_hba *phba "  ","
.BI "struct Scsi_Host *shost "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "phba" 12
pointer to lpfc hba data structure.
.IP "shost" 12
the shost to be used to detect Block guard settings.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine sets up the local Block guard protocol settings for \fIshost\fP.
This routine also allocates memory for debugging bg buffers.
